<TITLE> Workers Festival draws in thousands </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Narayanganj, Oct 24 (bdnews24.com)  The workers of readymade garment factories on Friday took part in a Workers Festival at Osmany Stadium at Isdair in the town. More than 50,000 workers from knitwear factories at Dhaka, Narayanganj, Gazipur and Savar joined the festival, the organisers, Bangladesh Knitwear Manufacturers and Exporters Association (BKMEA), said. BKMEA president Fazlul Hoque, who inaugurated the festival at 9am, said it was the first festival of its kind. The galleries of the stadium were brimming with male and female workers well ahead of the start of the festival. The stadium and the adjoining areas were decorated colourfully. RAB, police and personnel of intelligence agencies took up stringent security measures. Fire service, emergency medical teams and NGOs set up stall at the venue. The workers staged fashion show and dress-as-you-like, music, dance, recitation, jokes, magic show, paala gaan , drama and other competitions at the festival. Raffle draw was an attraction of the function. A number of winning workers received colour TV sets as prizes in the draw. The competitors of the dress-as-you-like event were also given colour TV sets as prizes. Each of some 50,000 workers was given a gift box. A village fair was organised outside the stadium. Monkey dance, doll dance, Nagor Dola , bioscope, horse and elephant rides added attraction to the fair. Hoque, the BKMEA president, said from now a workers festival would be organised every year as an extension of the knit exposition. Commerce adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman joined the festival in the afternoon and distributed prizes among the winners. The adviser expressed the hope that in future the owners of other industries would also organise such festivals. Singer Momtaz and Bari Siddiqui rendered songs at night. bdn
